n\nЕдинственное исключение - \"бонусные деньги\" для удержания. Не для привлечения.\n\nГлавные операторы Европы выстроились в очередь на рынок, где стандартный ретеншн-инструментарий - вне закона.\n\nРынок открылся. VIP - нет.\n\n@vipcare_io", "image_html": null}], "linkedin_post": {"text": "LINKEDIN POST:\n\nFinland is opening its iGaming market for the first time in the country's history. Flutter, Entain, LeoVegas, Betsson, Kindred - 24 operators have already entered the licensing queue ahead of the July 2027 launch.\n\nOne detail most VIP leaders aren't discussing: the new law explicitly prohibits VIP programs, loyalty schemes based on volume of play, and welcome bonuses. Not restricted - prohibited.\n\nFinland's €1.9B market will require private operators to retain players without the standard toolkit. No VIP tiers. No cashback-on-wager mechanics. No welcome splash. The regulation mandates a product-first, service-driven retention model.\n\nThe irony is hard to miss: Europe's largest operators are lining up for a market where their core retention mechanics are illegal. If bonus spend disappears, what keeps your players?\n\nMore markets will converge on this model. Finland is showing the template early. The question is whether your VIP program survives the transfer.\n\n#iGaming #VIPRetention #CasinoOperations #PlayerExperience"}}